20":null,"duedate":null,"customfield_12310250":null,"progress":{"progress":0,"total":0},"comment":{"startAt":0,"maxResults":11,"total":11,"comments":[{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12474495/comment/12911099","id":"12911099","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=scode","name":"scode","emailAddress":"peter dot schuller at infidyne dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Peter Schuller","active":true},"body":"Is the intent that entire-ring restarts (e.g. all your racks lose power at the same time) will not compromise the cluster? I.e., even with active clients writing actively, unaware of a problem, a ring can be restarted without risking any nodes going up believing they are alone (or similar) - even without special manual intervention on start-up?\r\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=scode","name":"scode","emailAddress":"peter dot schuller at infidyne dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Peter Schuller","active":true},"created":"2010-09-18T21:41:46.114+0000","updated":"2010-09-18T21:41:46.114+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12474495/comment/12911100","id":"12911100","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=brandon.williams","name":"brandon.williams","emailAddress":"driftx at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054"},"displayName":"Brandon Williams","active":true},"body":"I think Jonathan is just proposing that we enhance the token tracking we already perform.  State is never stored, that is the FailureDetector's job to determine on startup.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=brandon.williams","name":"brandon.williams","emailAddress":"driftx at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054"},"displayName":"Brandon Williams","active":true},"created":"2010-09-18T21:48:43.723+0000","updated":"2010-09-18T21:48:43.723+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12474495/comment/12911125","id":"12911125","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jbellis","name":"jbellis","emailAddress":"jbellis at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380"},"displayName":"Jonathan Ellis","active":true},"body":"right, this is to keep nodes from thinking they are responsible for more of the ring than they actually are in case of planned or unexpected cluster restarts.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jbellis","name":"jbellis","emailAddress":"jbellis at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380"},"displayName":"Jonathan Ellis","active":true},"created":"2010-09-19T00:14:12.167+0000","updated":"2010-09-19T00:14:12.167+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12474495/comment/12916322","id":"12916322","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=brandon.williams","name":"brandon.williams","emailAddress":"driftx at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054"},"displayName":"Brandon Williams","active":true},"body":"Patch to track remote tokens/endpoints in a new key in the system CF and load them on startup, unless -Dcassandra.load_ring_state is false.  To change the IPs in a cluster, this will need to be set.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=brandon.williams","name":"brandon.williams","emailAddress":"driftx at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054"},"displayName":"Brandon Williams","active":true},"created":"2010-09-30T00:32:00.780+0000","updated":"2010-09-30T00:32:00.780+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12474495/comment/12916334","id":"12916334","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jbellis","name":"jbellis","emailAddress":"jbellis at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380"},"displayName":"Jonathan Ellis","active":true},"body":"shouldn't CASSANDRA-1118 allow a new owner (old owner w/ new ip) to claim a token, even w/o the flag?","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jbellis","name":"jbellis","emailAddress":"jbellis at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380"},"displayName":"Jonathan Ellis","active":true},"created":"2010-09-30T01:15:44.541+0000","updated":"2010-09-30T01:15:44.541+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12474495/comment/12916339","id":"12916339","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=brandon.williams","name":"brandon.williams","emailAddress":"driftx at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054"},"displayName":"Brandon Williams","active":true},"body":"Yes, though addSavedEndpoint needs to set the heartbeat generation to something higher than zero.  The IP can take over the token at that point, but the state is never updated.   I'll have to investigate further.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=brandon.williams","name":"brandon.williams","emailAddress":"driftx at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054"},"displayName":"Brandon Williams","active":true},"created":"2010-09-30T01:40:36.423+0000","updated":"2010-09-30T01:40:36.423+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12474495/comment/12916607","id":"12916607","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=brandon.williams","name":"brandon.williams","emailAddress":"driftx at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054"},"displayName":"Brandon Williams","active":true},"body":"Updated patch allows tokens to be taken over by new IPs.  Note that I had to change some logic in StorageService for this to work:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nif (currentNode == null || (FBUtilities.getLocalAddress().equals(currentNode) && Gossiper.instance.compareEndpointStartup(endpoint, currentNode) > 0))\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThe problem here is if node X knows about token T belonging to node Y, and node Z tries to take over this token, X will refuse to allow it because Z is not X.  Instead:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nif (currentNode == null || Gossiper.instance.compareEndpointStartup(endpoint, currentNode) > 0)\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nWill always rely on the heartbeat generation to determine if the token ownership should be changed.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=brandon.williams","name":"brandon.williams","emailAddress":"driftx at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=brandon.williams&avatarId=10054"},"displayName":"Brandon Williams","active":true},"created":"2010-09-30T19:02:35.545+0000","updated":"2010-09-30T19:02:35.545+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12474495/comment/12916643","id":"12916643","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jbellis","name":"jbellis","emailAddress":"jbellis at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380"},"displayName":"Jonathan Ellis","active":true},"body":"committing the updateNormalToken change to 0.6, but not the rest of this.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jbellis","name":"jbellis","emailAddress":"jbellis at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380"},"displayName":"Jonathan Ellis","active":true},"created":"2010-09-30T20:33:19.936+0000","updated":"2010-09-30T20:33:19.936+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12474495/comment/12916655","id":"12916655","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jbellis","name":"jbellis","emailAddress":"jbellis at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org